main event: Three unidentified objects were observed moving at a high rate of speed in the middle of the sky over Nebraska, with the aid of a theodolite.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be twice the size of a pinhead and had uneven upper and lower illumination, flashing on and off.
The objects moved at a high rate of speed and soon disappeared from sight.
No sound was heard during the observation.
The report includes diagrams and maps, but no photographs.
The objects were observed by military personnel and civilian witnesses from multiple vantage points.
